BTW Integration test for the JSON stdlib module

I CAN HAS STDIO?
I CAN HAS JSON?
I CAN HAS TEST?

HAI ME TEH FUNCSHUN MAIN
    SAYZ WIT "Testing JSON module..."

    BTW TO_JSON: primitives
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_NULL TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT NOTHIN
    ASSERT WIT J_NULL SAEM AS "null"
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_TRUE TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT YEZ
    ASSERT WIT J_TRUE SAEM AS "true"
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_FALSE TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT NO
    ASSERT WIT J_FALSE SAEM AS "false"
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_INT TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT 42
    ASSERT WIT J_INT SAEM AS "42"
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_FLOAT TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT 3.14
    ASSERT WIT J_FLOAT SAEM AS "3.14"
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_STR TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT "hello"
    ASSERT WIT J_STR SAEM AS "\"hello\""

    BTW TO_JSON: BUKKIT array
    I HAS A VARIABLE ARR TEH BUKKIT ITZ NEW BUKKIT
    ARR DO PUSH WIT 1
    ARR DO PUSH WIT "two"
    ARR DO PUSH WIT YEZ
    I HAS A VARIABLE J_ARR TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT ARR
    ASSERT WIT J_ARR SAEM AS "[1,\"two\",true]"

    BTW TO_JSON + FROM_JSON round-trip for a BASKIT map
    BTW (Key order in JSON objects is not deterministic, so we test via round-trip)
    I HAS A VARIABLE MAP TEH BASKIT ITZ NEW BASKIT
    MAP DO PUT WIT "name" AN WIT "Alice"
    MAP DO PUT WIT "age" AN WIT 30
    I HAS A VARIABLE MAP_JSON TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT MAP
    I HAS A VARIABLE MAP_RT TEH BASKIT ITZ FROM_JSON WIT MAP_JSON
    I HAS A VARIABLE MAP_RT_NAME TEH STRIN ITZ MAP_RT DO GET WIT "name"
    I HAS A VARIABLE MAP_RT_AGE TEH DUBBLE ITZ MAP_RT DO GET WIT "age"
    ASSERT WIT MAP_RT_NAME SAEM AS "Alice"
    ASSERT WIT MAP_RT_AGE SAEM AS 30.0

    BTW FROM_JSON: primitives
    I HAS A VARIABLE FROM_NULL_VAL ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "null"
    ASSERT WIT FROM_NULL_VAL SAEM AS NOTHIN
    I HAS A VARIABLE FROM_TRUE TEH BOOL ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "true"
    ASSERT WIT FROM_TRUE SAEM AS YEZ
    I HAS A VARIABLE FROM_FALSE TEH BOOL ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "false"
    ASSERT WIT FROM_FALSE SAEM AS NO
    I HAS A VARIABLE FROM_NUM TEH DUBBLE ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "3.14"
    ASSERT WIT FROM_NUM SAEM AS 3.14
    I HAS A VARIABLE FROM_STR TEH STRIN ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "\"world\""
    ASSERT WIT FROM_STR SAEM AS "world"

    BTW FROM_JSON: array
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_ARR TEH BUKKIT ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "[10,20,30]"
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_ARR_SIZ TEH INTEGR ITZ PARSED_ARR SIZ
    ASSERT WIT PARSED_ARR_SIZ SAEM AS 3
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_ARR_0 TEH DUBBLE ITZ PARSED_ARR DO AT WIT 0
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_ARR_1 TEH DUBBLE ITZ PARSED_ARR DO AT WIT 1
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_ARR_2 TEH DUBBLE ITZ PARSED_ARR DO AT WIT 2
    ASSERT WIT PARSED_ARR_0 SAEM AS 10.0
    ASSERT WIT PARSED_ARR_1 SAEM AS 20.0
    ASSERT WIT PARSED_ARR_2 SAEM AS 30.0

    BTW FROM_JSON: object
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_OBJ TEH BASKIT ITZ FROM_JSON WIT "{\"x\":1,\"y\":2}"
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_X TEH DUBBLE ITZ PARSED_OBJ DO GET WIT "x"
    I HAS A VARIABLE PARSED_Y TEH DUBBLE ITZ PARSED_OBJ DO GET WIT "y"
    ASSERT WIT PARSED_X SAEM AS 1.0
    ASSERT WIT PARSED_Y SAEM AS 2.0

    BTW Round-trip: serialize nested structure then deserialize
    I HAS A VARIABLE INNER TEH BUKKIT ITZ NEW BUKKIT
    INNER DO PUSH WIT 99
    I HAS A VARIABLE OUTER TEH BASKIT ITZ NEW BASKIT
    OUTER DO PUT WIT "nums" AN WIT INNER
    I HAS A VARIABLE JSON_STR TEH STRIN ITZ TO_JSON WIT OUTER
    I HAS A VARIABLE RT TEH BASKIT ITZ FROM_JSON WIT JSON_STR
    I HAS A VARIABLE RT_NUMS TEH BUKKIT ITZ RT DO GET WIT "nums"
    I HAS A VARIABLE RT_FIRST TEH DUBBLE ITZ RT_NUMS DO AT WIT 0
    ASSERT WIT RT_FIRST SAEM AS 99.0

    SAYZ WIT "JSON tests passed!"
KTHXBAI
